/*
:name: mod_signed_dividend
:type: error
:tolg: 1
:error: possibly-negative
*/
// `a % 8` with a possibly-negative `a` has no hardware lowering: signed modulo
// semantics are language-dependent, so the easy power-of-two mask only applies
// to a non-negative dividend (tolg lower_mod).
comb foo(a:s8) -> (r) {
  r = a % 8
}
